{"title_page": "1978 Toronto Blue Jays season", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2013}}\n{{Infobox MLB yearly\n| name = Toronto Blue Jays\n| season = 1978\n| misc =\n| logo = \n| current league = American League\n| y1 = 1977\n| division = [[American League East|Eastern Division]]\n| y2 = 1977\n| Uniform logo =\n| ballpark = [[Exhibition Stadium]]\n| y4 = 1977\n| city = [[Toronto]]\n| y5 = 1977\n| record         = 59\u2013102 (.364)\n| divisional place = 7th\n| owners = [[Labatt Breweries]],<br>Imperial Trust,<br>[[Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce]]\n| general managers = [[Pat Gillick]]\n| managers = [[Roy Hartsfield]]\n| television = [[CBC Television]]<br>([[Don Chevrier]], [[Tony Kubek]], Tom McKee)<br>[[CBFT]]<br>([[Jean-Pierre Roy]], Guy Ferron)\n| radio = [[CJCL (AM)|CKFH]]<br>([[Early Wynn]], [[Tom Cheek]])\n|}}\nThe '''1978 [[Toronto Blue Jays]] season''' was the franchise's second season of [[Major League Baseball]]. It resulted in the Blue Jays finishing seventh in the [[American League East]] with a record of 59 wins and 102 losses.\n\n== Offseason ==\n* October 25, 1977: [[Phil Roof]] was released by the Blue Jays.<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/r/roofph01.shtml Phil Roof page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n* November 11, 1977: Luis Gomez was signed as a free agent by the Blue Jays.<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/players/g/gomezlu01.shtml Luis Gomez page] at Baseball-Reference</ref>\n* January 10, 1978: [[Geno Petralli]] was drafted by the Blue Jays in the 3rd round of the [[1978 Major League Baseball draft]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/p/petrage01.shtml Geno Petralli page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n* March 15, 1978: [[Dennis DeBarr]] was traded by the Blue Jays to the [[Cleveland Indians]] for [[Rico Carty]].<ref name=carty>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/c/cartyri01.shtml Rico Carty page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n* March 15, 1978: [[Tom Bruno]] and cash were traded by the Blue Jays to the [[St. Louis Cardinals]] for [[Rick Bosetti]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/b/bosetri01.shtml Rick Bosetti page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n\n== Regular season ==\n\n=== Opening Day starters ===\n* [[Alan Ashby]]\n* [[Bob Bailor]]\n* [[Rick Bosetti]]\n* [[Rico Carty]]\n* [[Jerry Garvin]]\n* [[Luis G\u00f3mez (baseball)|Luis G\u00f3mez]]\n* [[Roy Howell]]\n* [[Tommy Hutton]]\n* [[John Mayberry]]\n* [[Dave McKay (baseball)|Dave McKay]]\n\n=== Season standings ===\n{{1978 AL East standings}}\n\n=== Record vs. opponents ===\n{{1978 AL Record vs. opponents|team=TOR}}\n\n=== Notable transactions ===\n* April 4, 1978: [[John Mayberry]] was purchased by the Blue Jays from the [[Kansas City Royals]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/m/maybejo01.shtml John Mayberry page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n* May 22, 1978: [[Joe Coleman (1970s pitcher)|Joe Coleman]] was purchased by the Blue Jays from the [[Oakland Athletics]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/players/c/colemjo05.shtml Joe Coleman page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n* June 6, 1978: [[1978 Major League Baseball draft]]\n**[[Lloyd Moseby]] was drafted by the Blue Jays in the 1st round (2nd pick).<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/m/mosebll01.shtml Lloyd Moseby page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n**[[Dave Stieb]] was drafted by the Blue Jays in the 5th round.<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/s/stiebda01.shtml Dave Stieb page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n* August 15, 1978: [[Rico Carty]] was traded by the Blue Jays to the [[Oakland Athletics]] for [[Willie Horton (baseball)|Willie Horton]] and [[Phil Huffman]].<ref name=carty/>\n\n=== Roster ===\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"10\" style=\"background-color: #005ac0; color: white; text-align: center;\" | 1978 Toronto Blue Jays\n|-\n| colspan=\"10\" style=\"background-color: black; color: white; text-align: center;\" | '''Roster'''\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | '''Pitchers'''\n{{MLBplayer|44|[[Tom Buskey]]}}\n{{MLBplay