[Geno Petralli]] was drafted by the Blue Jays in the 3rd round of the [[1978 Major League Baseball draft]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/p/petrage01.shtml Geno Petralli page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n* March 15, 1978: [[Dennis DeBarr]] was traded by the Blue Jays to the [[Cleveland Indians]] for [[Rico Carty]].<ref name=carty>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/c/cartyri01.shtml Rico Carty page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n* March 15, 1978: [[Tom Bruno]] and cash were traded by the Blue Jays to the [[St. Louis Cardinals]] for [[Rick Bosetti]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/b/bosetri01.shtml Rick Bosetti page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n\n== Regular season ==\n\n=== Opening Day starters ===\n* [[Alan Ashby]]\n* [[Bob Bailor]]\n* [[Rick Bosetti]]\n* [[Rico Carty]]\n* [[Jerry Garvin]]\n* [[Luis G\u00f3mez (baseball)|Luis G\u00f3mez]]\n* [[Roy Howell]]\n* [[Tommy Hutton]]\n* [[John Mayberry]]\n* [[Dave McKay (baseball)|Dave McKay]]\n\n=== Season standings ===\n{{1978 AL East standings}}\n\n=== Record vs. opponents ===\n{{1978 AL Record vs. opponents|team=TOR}}\n\n=== Notable transactions ===\n* April 4, 1978: [[John Mayberry]] was purchased by the Blue Jays from the [[Kansas City Royals]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/m/maybejo01.shtml John Mayberry page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n* May 22, 1978: [[Joe Coleman (1970s pitcher)|Joe Coleman]] was purchased by the Blue Jays from the [[Oakland Athletics]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/players/c/colemjo05.shtml Joe Coleman page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n* June 6, 1978: [[1978 Major League Baseball draft]]\n**[[Lloyd Moseby]] was drafted by the Blue Jays in the 1st round (2nd pick).<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/m/mosebll01.shtml Lloyd Moseby page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n**[[Dave Stieb]] was drafted by the Blue Jays in the 5th round.<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/s/stiebda01.shtml Dave Stieb page] at Baseball Reference</ref>\n* August 15, 1978: 